<TITLE> NBR sues Babar for tax dodge </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 14 (bdnews24.com)  The National Board of Revenue has filed a case on Sunday against detained former state minister for home Lutfozzaman Babar for tax dodging. Syed Zakir Hossain, NBR deputy tax commissioner of tax area-3, filed the case with a Senior Special Judge's Court of Judge ANM Bashir Ullah. After a hearing, the court took the case into cognisance and issued arrest warrant against Babar. But as the accused was already detained in other cases, he was shown arrested in this one, said additional public prosecutor Shah Alam Talukder. He told bdnews24.com, "The court issued this arrest warrant as his previous detention was not listed in the case statement." The court also fixed February 23 for holding hearing on the case. The case statement said that the former state minister, as a director of Master Electronics Industry Limited, concealed income worth around Tk 86 million in 1999-2000 and 2008-2009 taxation years and evaded the tax counted on it. On Oct 30 last year, Babar was convicted of illegally possessing firearm and ammunition and sentenced to 17 years in jail. On Feb 2 this year, he was shown arrested in the Kibria murder case. He was also shown arrested in the Aug 21 grenade attack case. bdnew
